  "id": "",
  "summary": "Heavily obfuscated code in hidden.ad/ directory requires human review",
  "details": "The package ships ~45 JavaScript files inside a hidden `.ad/` directory (from-generator.js, phone-validator.js, sms-providers.js, smtp-health-cache.js, web-command.js, and a series x0.js–xz.js) that are heavily obfuscated using the hex-identifier scheme (variables of the form `_0xNNNNNN`). File names suggest SMS/SMTP/phone-validation/web-command tooling, but the contents are not human-readable as shipped, and source maps or unobfuscated equivalents are not present. Hidden-directory placement plus obfuscation across dozens of files is highly atypical for a legitimate npm library and is a strong indicator that the author is concealing the actual behavior from reviewers. Tracing of the obfuscated code to determine whether it performs credential theft, exfiltration, or remote code execution did not complete, so a concrete attacker-benefit mechanism cannot be cited from this run alone. Routing to human review for de-obfuscation and behavioral analysis before installer trust is granted.",
